commit.message: Fix missing "." in @INC for newer versions of perl
Detect accidental use of output file as input file

Merge changelog versions

Since I didn't release the other version yet

Adding test dependency.

Not sure if this is really needed. I have this uncommitted change and
can't remember why it's there.

Use warnings instead of -w in shebang

Using -w can cause grepmail being prevented from running if a library
is emitting warnings.

Debian bug reference: https://bugs.debian.org/584728
Add standard tests, and make them pass

Miscellaneous fixes for Windows compatibility

This includes weaking the invalid mailbox test so that it only looks for output
from grepmail, and not any "broken pipe" message from the OS.
Require File::Slurp instead of including it, to avoid potential problems

Move verbose testing to a private module, and implement it in a way that doesn't require editing the Makefile after it is generated.

Also use a newer version of CheckOptional that declares its own Module::AutoInstall requirement.
